<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10216464>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Aloe gariepensis. A. Known distribution (red shading). B. Small, single, acaulescent rosette with short, uniform yellow inflorescences. C. Rosette of reddish brown, clearly lineate leaves with no white spots. D. Big, caulescent rosette with tall, bicoloured inflorescences. E. Yellow buds and flowers on a unicoloured raceme. F. Red buds and yellow open flowers on a bicoloured raceme. Photographs: Arrie W. Klopper (B, C. Grootderm, near Orange River, Northern Cape, South Africa; D–F. Warmbad, Namibia; July 2010)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10216464/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

